-- Sarkozy, Hollande Neck and Neck in First-Round Presidential Poll
-- B y   H e l e n e   F o u q u e t
-- 2012-02-27T17:55:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-27/sarkozy-hollande-neck-and-neck-in-first-round-presidential-poll.html
French Socialist presidential
candidate Francois Hollande and the incumbent,  Nicolas Sarkozy ,
remained  neck and neck  in first-round support, according to the
daily Ifop tracking poll.  Hollande has 28 percent backing and Sarkozy 27 percent in
the April 22 first round of the election, both up half a
percentage point from Feb. 24, according to Ifop. The National
Front’s Marine Le Pen has 17.5 percent support,  Francois Bayrou 
of the centrist Democratic Movement 12 percent support and Left
Front candidate Jean-Luc Melanchon 9 percent.  For the second round on May 6, Hollande’s lead narrowed to
55.5 percent against 44.5 for Sarkozy, compared with a 12-point
lead in the previous poll.  Paris-based Ifop interviewed 882 registered voters through
an internet questionnaire. The survey, conducted every day
except weekends, is published by  Paris Match magazine .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helene Fouquet in Paris at 
